## Description
Optionally provide a method as value of the `nRowsSelected` prop on the `toolbar.localization` object to generate the plural/singular string, based on the row count.

In English, "row(s)", might be accepted, but in many languages pluralisation isn't that clean and you often need completely different words. This helps me in creating a context-aware translation.

It is completely opt-in, so it won't break any of the existing string-based localisation.

## Example
The following will result in "1 row selected" when there is only one selected, "x rows selected" otherwise.
```typescript
<MaterialTable
  localization={{
    toolbar: {
      nRowsSelected: (rowCount) => `${rowCount} ${rowCount === 1 ? 'row' : 'rows'} selected`,
    },
  }}
/>
```

